Replanning would be correct if `step-001` had shown that no intrinsic object
survived, that the search class was still noncanonical, or that the next move
should no longer follow the chain's declared order. The step shows the
opposite. It resolves the exact definitional and methodology gates that the
planning run said had to be fixed before support enumeration could mean
anything. Sending the mission back to planning now would discard a branch
