+
+## Mission Context
+
+**Mission:** Exact NS Phase-Locking Firewall
+
+**Active chain:**
+`Chain 01 - Intrinsic Exact Closed-Support Delayed-Transfer Stress Test`
+
+**Why this step exists now:** `step-002` exhausted the first rung honestly.
+It fixed the one-triad seed catalog, showed that every honest one-triad seed
+spills outside the one-triad budget once conjugate completion and full-ledger
+recursive closure are enforced, and showed that the mirror-complete
+`{ ±p, ±q, ±k }`
+picture fails the required admissible-enlargement audit. That is a
+budget-limited negative on rung 1, not a chain kill. The frozen escalation
+ladder therefore points next to the second rung:
+**two-triad shared-mode clusters**.
+
+## This Step Covers
+
+This strategizer execution covers **Chain Step 2 only**, now at the **second
+declared budget**.
+
+For this branch, the current budget is the second rung of the frozen Step-1
+escalation ladder:
+**two exact triad orbits sharing a mode on the canonical helical support
+sheet, up to the frozen equivalence rules**.
+
+You must do all of the following, and only the following:
+
+- define the canonical second-budget seed families for two-triad shared-mode
+  clusters, modulo the Step-1 equivalence rules and the Step-2 first-budget
+  exclusions;
+- make explicit which apparent two-triad pictures are genuinely new second-rung
+  seeds and which are only disguised first-budget dead seeds or inert
+  decorations;
+- apply mandatory conjugate completion and recursive exact closure to each
+  seed, including all nonzero projected triad interactions and all forced
+  helical sign sectors;
+- keep every closure-forced mode in the support ledger immediately, including
+  modes that function only as spectators or companions;
+- decide for each seed whether recursive closure reaches a genuine finite fixed
+  point inside the current budget, spills beyond the budget, loses exactness,
+  or remains representation-dependent;
+- run at least one admissible enlargement test on every apparent survivor;
+- record the exact support ledger for every survivor and the decisive failure
+  reason for every dead seed; and
+- state whether any second-budget survivor now makes Chain Step 3 well posed.
+  If none do, package only a budget-limited negative result for controller
+  review. Do **not** execute the third ladder rung in this step.
+
+Do **not** derive full projected ODEs yet. That still belongs to Chain Step 3.
+Do **not** solve phase-compatibility or slow-drift conditions yet. That also
+belongs to Chain Step 3.
+Do **not** score delayed-transfer windows, spectator burden, or robustness yet.
+That belongs to Chain Step 4.
+
+## Frozen Commitments From Earlier Steps
+
+The following freezes remain binding in this step unless you discover an
+explicit contradiction in the exact local record:
+
+- carry the intrinsic object forward as the exact triad-phase orbit measure
+  `Mu_S`;
+- use finite helical support ledgers as the exact search objects, not
+  packet-role objects;
+- require mandatory conjugate completion and recursive exact closure from the
+  start;
+- include closure-forced spectator modes immediately in the exact support
+  ledger rather than pruning them away;
+- treat the two Step-1 admissible enlargements as live tests on any apparent
+  survivor;
+- keep smallest-first ordering and the frozen escalation ladder;
+- keep every negative claim class-limited to the current ladder level and
+  budget; and
+- preserve the Step-1 metric sheet unchanged for later steps, but do not use
+  it yet to claim dynamic success.
+
+The following Step-2 outcomes are also now frozen and must be treated as prior
+control facts rather than rediscovered from scratch:
+
+- the one-triad budget is exhausted:
+  no genuinely invariant finite support survives there;
+- repeated-wavevector and collinear "triads" are not honest live seeds for
+  this branch;
+- the canonical one-triad sign-sheet classes
+  `(+++)`,
+  `(++-)`,
+  and
+  `(+--)`
+  already died by budget spill on the first honest closure pass; and
+- the mirror-complete six-wavevector picture
+  `{ ±p, ±q, ±k }`
+  is a pseudo-survivor only and cannot be reused as a live exact support claim.
+
+## Required Deliverables
+
+Produce all of the following inside `RESULTS.md`:
+
+1. **Second-budget seed catalog**
+   - state the canonical representative families for two-triad shared-mode
+     clusters;
+   - state the equivalence reductions used to avoid duplicate seeds;
+   - explain why the catalog is honest for the current budget rather than a
+     cherry-picked subset or a recycled rung-1 picture.
+
+2. **Recursive closure ledger**
+   - for each seed, list the closure operations in order:
+     conjugates,
+     forced helical sectors,
+     and all newly forced triad interactions;
+   - show whether the process reaches a finite fixed point or spills out;
+   - identify every closure-forced spectator or companion mode explicitly.
+
+3. **Admissible-enlargement audit**
+   - apply at least one admissible enlargement test to every apparent
+     survivor;
+   - state whether the survivor remains genuinely finite and exact under that
+     enlargement or was an artifact of over-pruning;
+   - name the decisive reason for each survivor's survival or failure.
+
+4. **Budget-limited verdict**
+   - state whether any genuinely invariant finite support survives at the
+     second budget;
+   - if yes, name the survivor set that Chain Step 3 must inherit;
+   - if no, state the sharpest earned current-budget negative:
+     recursive closure explosion,
+     no exact finite fixed point,
+     enlargement failure,
+     or another precise budget-limited obstruction;
+   - state whether Chain Step 3 is now well posed on any survivor, or whether
+     controller review is needed before further escalation.
