+# Step 4 Goal: Chain Step 2 Enumerate Canonical Recursively Closed Supports Inside The Three-Triad Repeated-Wavevector Cross-Scale Budget
+
+## Mission Context
+
+**Mission:** Exact NS Phase-Locking Firewall
+
+**Active chain:**
+`Chain 01 - Intrinsic Exact Closed-Support Delayed-Transfer Stress Test`
+
+**Why this step exists now:** `step-003` exhausted the second rung honestly.
+It fixed the canonical two-triad shared-mode catalog, showed that every honest
+second-budget seed spills outside the current budget once conjugate completion
+and full-ledger recursive closure are enforced, and showed that the only tidy
+pseudo-survivors also fail the required admissible-enlargement audit. That is a
+budget-limited negative on rung 2, not a chain kill. The frozen escalation
+ladder therefore points next to the third rung:
+**three-triad clusters with one repeated wavevector orbit across two scales**.
+
+This is still the right next move after `step-003` because no reserve branch has
+been activated by the current record:
+there is no exact survivor to hand off to a finite-compatibility branch, and no
+intrinsicity collapse that would force a return to the scoped-audit branch.
+The branch remains construction-facing, but only through the next smallest
+budget that is genuinely new after the rung-1 and rung-2 deaths.
+
+## This Step Covers
+
+This strategizer execution covers **Chain Step 2 only**, now at the **third
+declared budget**.
+
+For this branch, the current budget is the third rung of the frozen Step-1
+escalation ladder:
+**connected three-triad seed clusters on the canonical helical support sheet in
+which one wavevector orbit is reused across two distinct scale levels, up to
+the frozen equivalence rules and the lower-budget exclusions**.
+
+You must do all of the following, and only the following:
+
+- define the canonical third-budget seed families for connected three-triad
+  repeated-wavevector cross-scale clusters, modulo the Step-1 equivalence rules
+  and the Step-2 and Step-3 exclusions;
+- make explicit which apparent three-triad pictures are genuinely new
+  third-rung seeds and which are only disguised first-budget or second-budget
+  dead seeds, inert decorations, or disconnected add-ons;
+- apply mandatory conjugate completion and recursive exact closure to each
+  seed, including all nonzero projected triad interactions and all forced
+  helical sign sectors;
+- keep every closure-forced mode in the support ledger immediately, including
+  modes that function only as spectators or companions;
+- decide for each seed whether recursive closure reaches a genuine finite fixed
+  point inside the current budget, spills beyond the budget, loses exactness,
+  or remains representation-dependent;
+- run at least one admissible enlargement test on every apparent survivor;
+- record the exact support ledger for every survivor and the decisive failure
+  reason for every dead seed; and
+- state whether any third-budget survivor now makes Chain Step 3 well posed.
+  If none do, package only a budget-limited negative result for controller
+  review. Do **not** execute the fourth ladder rung in this step.
+
+Do **not** derive full projected ODEs yet. That still belongs to Chain Step 3.
+Do **not** solve phase-compatibility or slow-drift conditions yet. That also
+belongs to Chain Step 3.
+Do **not** score delayed-transfer windows, spectator burden, or robustness yet.
+That belongs to Chain Step 4.
+
+## Frozen Commitments From Earlier Steps
+
+The following freezes remain binding in this step unless you discover an
+explicit contradiction in the exact local record:
+
+- carry the intrinsic object forward as the exact triad-phase orbit measure
+  `Mu_S`;
+- use finite helical support ledgers as the exact search objects, not
+  packet-role objects;
+- require mandatory conjugate completion and recursive exact closure from the
+  start;
+- include closure-forced spectator modes immediately in the exact support
+  ledger rather than pruning them away;
+- treat the two Step-1 admissible enlargements as live tests on any apparent
+  survivor;
+- keep smallest-first ordering and the frozen escalation ladder;
+- keep every negative claim class-limited to the current ladder level and
+  budget; and
+- preserve the Step-1 metric sheet unchanged for later steps, but do not use
+  it yet to claim dynamic success.
+
+The following earlier outcomes are also now frozen and must be treated as prior
+control facts rather than rediscovered from scratch:
+
+- the one-triad budget is exhausted:
+  no genuinely invariant finite support survives there;
+- the canonical two-triad shared-mode budget is exhausted:
+  no genuinely invariant finite support survives there either;
+- repeated-wavevector and collinear "triads" are not honest live seeds for this
+  branch;
+- the generic five-orbit shared-mode fan and the mirror/parallelogram subfamily
+  are dead second-rung families, not reusable survivors; and
+- the lower-budget pseudo-survivors already failed admissible-enlargement
+  review and cannot be revived as live exact supports by cosmetic redrawing.
+
+## Required Deliverables
+
+Produce all of the following inside `RESULTS.md`:
+
+1. **Third-budget seed catalog**
+   - state the canonical representative families for connected three-triad
+     repeated-wavevector cross-scale clusters;
+   - state the equivalence reductions used to avoid duplicate seeds;
+   - explain why the catalog is honest for the current budget rather than a
+     cherry-picked subset or a recycled lower-budget picture.
+
+2. **Recursive closure ledger**
+   - for each seed, list the closure operations in order:
+     conjugates,
+     forced helical sectors,
+     and all newly forced triad interactions;
+   - show whether the process reaches a finite fixed point or spills out;
+   - identify every closure-forced spectator or companion mode explicitly.
+
+3. **Admissible-enlargement audit**
+   - apply at least one admissible enlargement test to every apparent
+     survivor;
+   - state whether the survivor remains genuinely finite and exact under that
+     enlargement or was an artifact of over-pruning;
+   - name the decisive reason for each survivor's survival or failure.
+
+4. **Budget-limited verdict**
+   - state whether any genuinely invariant finite support survives at the third
+     budget;
+   - if yes, name the survivor set that Chain Step 3 must inherit;
+   - if no, state the sharpest earned current-budget negative:
+     recursive closure explosion,
+     no exact finite fixed point,
+     enlargement failure,
+     or another precise budget-limited obstruction;
+   - state whether Chain Step 3 is now well posed on any survivor, or whether
+     controller review is needed before further escalation.
+
+## Exploration Scope
+
+Use **2-3 explorations total** unless a kill condition fires early.
+
+Rely first on the frozen Step-1, Step-2, and Step-3 records and the current
+mission files:
+
+- `missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/steps/step-001/RESULTS.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/steps/step-001/REASONING.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/steps/step-001/HISTORY-OF-REPORT-SUMMARIES.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/steps/step-002/RESULTS.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/steps/step-002/REASONING.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/steps/step-002/HISTORY-OF-REPORT-SUMMARIES.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/steps/step-003/RESULTS.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/steps/step-003/REASONING.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/steps/step-003/HISTORY-OF-REPORT-SUMMARIES.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/CHAIN.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/CHAIN-HISTORY.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/MISSION.md`
+
+Do **not** spend this step on a broad new literature pass or a generic exact-NS
+survey. The point now is honest third-budget support enumeration under the
+already frozen object, closure rules, metric sheet, and lower-budget
+exclusions.
+
+## Suggested Exploration Split
+
+### Exploration A: Canonical third-budget seed classification
+
+Tasks:
+- classify distinct connected three-triad repeated-wavevector cross-scale seed
+  families under the frozen equivalence rules;
+- decide which candidate clusters are genuinely new third-rung seeds and which
+  are only disguised lower-budget failures or inert decorations;
+- produce the canonical seed catalog for the current budget.
+
+Success standard:
+- the step can enumerate the third budget without hidden representation choices
+  or recycled rung-1 or rung-2 artifacts.
+
+### Exploration B: Recursive closure and spillover audit
+
+Tasks:
+- run recursive exact closure on each canonical seed;
+- track all forced conjugates, helical sectors, and newly forced interactions;
+- determine which seeds reach genuine finite fixed points and which spill out.
+
+Success standard:
+- every seed ends with either an exact finite closure ledger or a precise
+  spillover or exactness-failure diagnosis.
+
+### Exploration C: Enlargement check and controller handoff
+
+Only run this after at least one apparent survivor exists, or after the branch
+has earned a clean current-budget negative.
+
+Tasks:
+- test every apparent survivor against at least one admissible enlargement;
+- decide whether any survivor remains alive for Chain Step 3;
+- package the budget-limited verdict for controller review.
+
+Success standard:
+- mission control receives either frozen survivors for exact dynamics work or a
+  clean third-budget obstruction memo.
+
+## Kill Conditions
+
+Trigger an early negative conclusion for this step if any of the following
+happens:
+
+- no canonical third-budget seed catalog can be stated without hidden
+  representation choices;
+- every seed loses exactness, spills outside the current budget, or fails the
+  admissible-enlargement check;
+- an apparent survivor exists only after dropping closure-forced spectator
+  modes, suppressing forced helical sectors, or gluing a dead lower-budget
+  picture to an inert extra triad;
+- the step cannot distinguish a true finite exact fixed point from a disguised
+  lower-budget artifact or another representation artifact.
+
+If any of those occur, report the sharpest earned **budget-limited** negative
+result and stop at the current budget. Do not overclaim a firewall-level
+failure and do not self-escalate to the next rung.
+
+## Constraints
+
+- Do **not** derive the full projected ODEs yet.
+- Do **not** solve compatibility equations for constant-phase or slow-drift
+  regimes yet.
+- Do **not** score delayed transfer, spectator burden, or robustness yet.
+- Do **not** use packet-role families as the search object, even if they help
+  suggest seeds.
+- Do **not** treat a cosmetically tidy three-triad picture as a survivor unless
+  recursive exact closure and enlargement checks both pass.
+- Do **not** make any negative claim broader than the current budget.
+
+## Validation Requirements
+
+- Tag each major conclusion as `[VERIFIED]`, `[INFERRED]`, or `[PROPOSED]`.
+- Name the exact local source files supporting each mission-context claim.
+- For every apparent survivor, give the exact mode ledger, the active triad
+  orbit list, and the reason the closure really is a fixed point.
+- For every dead seed, name the decisive failure reason in one line.
+- Make the enlargement audit explicit enough that controller can tell whether
+  Chain Step 3 is truly earned or only cosmetically tempting.
+- If the step succeeds, end with one short section called
+  `Frozen supports for Chain Step 3`.
+- If the step does not produce a survivor, end with one short section called
